Array Outlines:

	- a group of like-typed variables that are referred to by a common name.
	- can have one or more dimensions
	
	One-dimension array
		- a list of liked-typed variables.
		- create array variable of desired type.
		
		//declare
		int month_days[];
		
		//allocate memory with new
		month_days = new int[12];
		
		- The elements in the array allocated by new will automatically be initialised to:
			:- 0 for numeric
			:- false for boolean
			:- null for reference types (objects and strings)
			
	Multidimension array
		- arrays or arrays
		- dimensions are based on the number of brackets
		
		int twoD[][] = new int[4][5];